say_hello[source]

say_hello(to)

Say hello to somebody

say_hello('mathew')

'Hello mathew!'
test_eq(say_hello('jenny'), "Hello jenny!")

class HelloSayer[source]

HelloSayer(to)

Say hello to to using say_hello

The HelloSayer class is intended for use by those who like to use classes where a simple function would suffice.

HelloSayer.say[source]

HelloSayer.say()

o = HelloSayer('bill')
o.say()

'Hello bill!'

bubble_scatter[source]

bubble_scatter(n)

Create a scatter plot of n different sized bubbles

bubble_scatter(50)
